 {"id":"remote_compilation_helper-o721","title":"Add test-specific timeout handling and configuration","description":"## Context & Background

Tests can have very different duration characteristics compared to builds:
- Some test suites run in seconds
- Integration tests might take minutes
- End-to-end tests might take tens of minutes
- Tests with --ignored flag run slow tests

## Current State

Looking at the codebase, timeout handling is:
- SSH execution has implicit timeouts
- No CompilationKind-specific timeout configuration
- Long-running tests might timeout unexpectedly

## Problem

1. Default timeouts may be too short for integration tests
2. No way to configure per-command-type timeouts
3. Agent might see unexpected timeouts for legitimate slow tests

## Proposed Solution

### 1. Add test-specific timeout configuration
```toml
[compilation.timeouts]
default = 300          # 5 minutes default
cargo_build = 600      # 10 minutes for builds
cargo_test = 1800      # 30 minutes for tests
cargo_clippy = 300     # 5 minutes for clippy
```

### 2. Parse timeout from command if present
```rust
fn parse_test_timeout(command: &str) -> Option<Duration> {
    // cargo test -- --timeout 60
    // Parse and use if present
}
```

### 3. Add --timeout flag to wrapped command if needed
```rust
fn wrap_with_timeout(command: &str, timeout: Duration) -> String {
    // Use timeout(1) command on Linux
    format!(\"timeout {} {}\", timeout.as_secs(), command)
}
```

### 4. Consider heartbeat/progress detection
- If output is streaming, reset timeout on each line
- Only timeout if no output for extended period

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Test-specific timeout configurable
- [ ] Long-running tests don't timeout unexpectedly
- [ ] Timeout messages are clear and actionable
- [ ] Command-embedded timeouts respected

## Files to Modify

