 {"id":"remote_compilation_helper-o9s","title":"Add toolchain field to protocol and transfer pipeline","description":"## Parent Epic: Automatic Toolchain Synchronization (remote_compilation_helper-ayn)

## Task Description

Extend the RCH protocol to include toolchain information in selection requests and execution requests. The worker needs to know which toolchain to use for compilation.

## Changes Required

### 1. Update SelectionRequest
```rust
// In rch-common/src/protocol.rs

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct SelectionRequest {
    pub project_id: String,
    pub required_cores: u32,
    pub preferred_workers: Vec<String>,
    pub toolchain: Option<ToolchainInfo>,  // NEW
}
```

### 2. Update Daemon API Parsing
```rust
// In rchd/src/api.rs

// Parse toolchain from query params or body
fn parse_selection_request(request: &Request) -> Result<SelectionRequest> {
    // ... existing parsing ...

    // Parse toolchain if provided
    let toolchain = query.get("toolchain")
        .map(|s| serde_json::from_str(s))
        .transpose()?;

    Ok(SelectionRequest {
        // ... existing fields ...
        toolchain,
    })
}
```

### 3. Update ExecutionRequest (Worker Protocol)
```rust
// In rch-common/src/protocol.rs or worker protocol

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct ExecutionRequest {
    pub command: String,
    pub working_dir: PathBuf,
    pub env: HashMap<String, String>,
    pub toolchain: Option<ToolchainInfo>,  // NEW
}
```

### 4. Update Transfer Pipeline
```rust
// In rch/src/transfer.rs

impl TransferPipeline {
    /// Execute command on remote worker with toolchain
    pub async fn execute_remote(
        &self,
        worker: &WorkerConfig,
        command: &str,
        toolchain: Option<&ToolchainInfo>,
    ) -> Result<ExecutionResult> {
        let wrapped_command = match toolchain {
            Some(tc) => format!(
                "rustup run {} {}",
                tc.rustup_toolchain(),
                command
            ),
            None => command.to_string(),
        };

        self.ssh_client.execute(&wrapped_command).await
    }
}
```

### 5. Update Hook to Pass Toolchain
```rust
// In rch/src/hook.rs

async fn handle_compilation(command: &str, project_root: &Path) -> HookDecision {
    // Detect toolchain
    let toolchain = detect_toolchain(project_root).ok();

    // Include in selection request
    let request = SelectionRequest {
        project_id: project_id.clone(),
        required_cores: estimate_cores(command),
        preferred_workers: vec![],
        toolchain: toolchain.clone(),
    };

    // ... query daemon ...

    // Include in execution
    let result = pipeline.execute_remote(
        &worker,
        command,
        toolchain.as_ref(),
    ).await;
}
```

## Protocol Wire Format

The toolchain can be sent as:
1. Query parameter (URL-encoded JSON)
2. Request body (for POST requests)
3. Custom header

Recommended: URL-encoded JSON in query param for GET, body for POST.

```
GET /select-worker?project=foo&cores=4&toolchain=%7B%22channel%22%3A%22nightly%22%2C%22date%22%3A%222024-01-15%22%7D
```

Or cleaner with POST body:
```json
{
  "project_id": "foo",
  "required_cores": 4,
  "toolchain": {
    "channel": "nightly",
    "date": "2024-01-15"
  }
}
```

## Files to Modify
- `rch-common/src/protocol.rs` or `rch-common/src/types.rs`
- `rchd/src/api.rs`
- `rch/src/hook.rs`
- `rch/src/transfer.rs`

## Testing
```rust
#[test]
fn test_selection_request_with_toolchain() {
    let request = SelectionRequest {
        project_id: "test".to_string(),
        required_cores: 4,
        preferred_workers: vec![],
        toolchain: Some(ToolchainInfo {
            channel: "nightly".to_string(),
            date: Some("2024-01-15".to_string()),
            full_version: "nightly-2024-01-15".to_string(),
        }),
    };

    let json = serde_json::to_string(&request).unwrap();
    let parsed: SelectionRequest = serde_json::from_str(&json).unwrap();

    assert_eq!(parsed.toolchain.unwrap().channel, "nightly");
}

#[test]
fn test_command_wrapping_with_toolchain() {
    let tc = ToolchainInfo {
        channel: "nightly".to_string(),
        date: Some("2024-01-15".to_string()),
        full_version: "".to_string(),
    };

    let wrapped = wrap_command("cargo build", Some(&tc));
    assert_eq!(wrapped, "rustup run nightly-2024-01-15 cargo build");
}

#[test]
fn test_command_no_wrapping_without_toolchain() {
    let wrapped = wrap_command("cargo build", None);
    assert_eq!(wrapped, "cargo build");
}
```

